this leads me to believe that since nod is a mirror image of the waking world with magical changes, that instead of a studio or workshop there is a street named sesame street and it is home to monsters, fairies, large birds, baby bears, and humans who all live together.

these instructions can also lead one to kaufman astoria studios where the show sesame street is filmed. however, there is also a real sesame street in new york. the intersection of west 63rd and broadway is named sesame street. this is due to sesame workshop being located there.

however, we can get even more specific than that. in previous questions of where sesame street is located and how to get there. we are given information that states the count says one takes the r train to steinway, walks a block and arrive at the street.

in 2017, the cast of sesame street were featured in a wired autocomplete interview. in said interview, the question of if sesame street is in new york is asked. one of the answers is given by grover who says that it is in the sixth borough. https://t.co/t4sSRydUoT
while it may just seem like a stretch, there is actual evidence that the inhabitants of sesame street are also inhabitants of the sixth borough.
nod is home to dream entities and is almost magical. anything that someone can dream, can happen in nod. what is to say that fuzzy monsters who all live in a neighborhood can’t be dreamt up?

okay so in the world of the unsleeping city, new york is made up of six boroughs. five of these boroughs are what we in real life have. however, they have a sixth borough called nod. nod is the home to the dreaming and the realm of dreams.
